evidence: A high light yield is also important-the crystal must convert as much gamma energy as possible into visible light, maximizing signal for efficient detection.

concepts.term: Have an emission wavelength near 400 nm; this wavelength represents the point of maximum sensitivity for standard PMTs

evidence: Have a large effective atomic number, which also results in a high γ-ray detection efficiency due to γ-ray absorption via photoelectric interactions
triples.o: high γ-ray detection efficiency via photoelectric interactions
